            "answer_text": "Bear in mind that among primates in general, humans are actually VERY peaceful.  If gorillas, chimps, or god forbid a monkey of any type were to enter a train or an airplane together, fewer would come out than went in and many would be missing fingers, eyes, or testicles. As to the causes of violence among humans, the answer is unknown but surely some very complex combination of inborn aggression plus environment plus rearing plus outside social conditions- probably much more the latter two. But don't think of humans as especially violent as a species- we aren't.  We're especially restrained and cooperative. ",
